@{FG Shine}Welcome to @{B}AmiChannel News@{UB}@{FG Text}

Hello and welcome to the 6th issue of @{B}AmiChannel News@{UB}.

Only  4 days for Christmas. And 11 for the New Year. So first of all, I wish you
a merry Christmas and a Happy New Year!!!!!

While  I  am  writing  this editorial (today is 20th December 1998) the time for
preordering  the 3dfx add-on for the @{B}Picasso IV@{UB} card is up. An add-on which will
be highly supported through @{B}Warp3D@{UB}.

At  this  moment, I don't know if the 500 needed preorders have been reached. If
this is not the case, it would be a real pity. And a missed oportunity.

If  there is something that every @{B}Amiga@{UB} owner want, it is the freedom to choose.
At  this  moment  only @{B}Phase 5@{UB} succeed in bringing real power to the @{B}Amiga@{UB}. With
the  recent release of the @{B}Bvision PPC@{UB}, @{B}A1200@{UB} users have at least a graphic crad
designed  for them. And big boxes @{B}Amiga@{UB} users have got the @{B}Cyberstorm PPC@{UB} option
for a log time now.

But  @{B}Escena@{UB}  announced  last  month a @{B}G3@{UB} card for @{B}Zorro III@{UB} equipped @{B}Amiga@{UB}s. And
@{B}Village Tronic@{UB} announce the possibility of the add-on for the @{B}Picasso IV@{UB} card. I
though this will be my chance. Although the @{B}Escena@{UB} board could be a vapour card,
if it is finally released there won't be any excuse to not upgrade.

As  an  @{B}A4000@{UB}  user,  I  could  choose  between the @{B}Phase 5@{UB} solution (@{B}Cyberstorm
PPC@{UB}/@{B}Cybervision  PPC@{UB})  and  the  @{B}Escena@{UB}/@{B}Village  Tronic@{UB}  combo. Only if the 3Dfx
add-on  is  relased.  I risked, and I have preordered. And I want to win. But if
the 3Dfx is not developed, the only choice will be the @{B}PowerUp@{UB} card.

By  the  way,  once  the  @{B}Bvision  PPC@{UB}  has  been  released, a lot of people are
expecting  what  will  be the next move of @{B}Phase 5@{UB}. It is uncertain if they will
keep  developing  for  the  @{B}Amiga@{UB}.  They  are dissapointed with the @{B}Amiga@{UB} users,
because some of them are only happy if they complain about everything.

Unlike  other  people  (I  am  thinking about some Sioux City based company ;)),
@{B}Phase  5@{UB}  deserve our eternal gratitude. They have made very good hardware. They
have brought the real power of the @{B}PPC@{UB} to the @{B}Amiga@{UB}. And their graphic cards are
great. Thanks a lot, @{B}Phase 5@{UB}.

Whatever  they  left the @{B}Amiga@{UB} scene or not, I only hope one thing from them: to
remove  the  @{B}WarpOS@{UB}  incompatibility  from  the @{B}PowerUp@{UB} cards. As @{B}Warp3D@{UB} will be
@{B}WarpOS@{UB}  based (it is being developed by @{B}Haage&Partner@{UB}), it has to be possible to
run  a  @{B}PowerUp@{UB} program and a @{B}WarpUp@{UB} program at once, for the sake of the future
developments (@{B}Explorer 2260@{UB}, @{B}WipeOut 2097@{UB}, @{B}Phoenix@{UB}, etc.)

The  next  issue  of  @{B}AmiChannel  News@{UB}  will feature an special report about the
things  that  have  happenned in 1998. And we will try to guess what will happen
next year. But this is another story.

Remember to visit the @{B}SAUG@{UB} website, which is located in:

         @{B}http://www.saug.com/news.html@{UB}

or you can visit its mirrors located in:

         @{B}http://soporte.databasedm.es/amiga/sau/@{UB}

And if you want to contribute to this effort, you can send your articles to:

         @{I}angel@saug.org @{UI}

Thanks for reading and I hope you enjoy this issue.

===============================================================================
