@node not02 "DELFINA 1200 - NEW DSP AUDIO CARD FOR AMIGA 1200"

@{B}DELFINA 1200@{UB} - NEW DSP AUDIO CARD FOR @{B}AMIGA 1200@{UB}
------------------------------------------------

@{I}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE@{UI}

@{I}1. TECH@{UI}

@{B}Delfina  1200@{UB} is based on @{B}Delfina Lite@{UB}, the most successful DSP card on @{B}Zorro-II
Amiga@{UB}s.  The  main difference between these two is that @{B}Delfina 1200@{UB} connects to
the internal clock port of @{B}A1200@{UB}. This way the @{B}PCMCIA@{UB} and expansion slots can be
used for other devices. The modern manufacturing allows a very low price: SRP is
$299.

@{B}Delfina  1200@{UB} is primarily a DSP audio card, and it is best suited for producing
and  recording  audio  with optional realtime effects. Effects can be applied on
any  sound  produced  by  @{B}Delfina@{UB}  or external source transparently, and all the
sounds produced by @{B}Delfina@{UB}-capable programs or external source can be mixed into
@{B}Delfina@{UB}'s  output.  @{B}Delfina  1200@{UB}  is  also  freely programmable for all general
computing tasks using the supplied compiler and libraries.

Features:
   * 37 MHz @{B}Motorola DSP56002@{UB} digital signal processor
       - 18.5 MIPS, upto 110 MOPS
       - 24 bit data bus (144 dB dynamic range)
   * 96kB (32kWords) SRAM
       - Zero-waitstate (12ns)
   * St-reo audio codec (Crystal CS4231A)
       - Sample frequencies upto 48 kHz at 16 bit
       - Three stereo inputs, one stereo output
       - All inputs can be mixed with Delfina's output
       - Full duplex recording and playback
       - One stereo RCA input
       - One stereo 3.5mm input with optional 20dB mic amplifier
       - One stereo RCA output
       - Internal connector for audio input from CD-ROM
       - Fully programmable using the supplied software
       - Registered version of @{B}SoundFX 3.50@{UB} software included

Requirements:
   * @{B}Amiga 1200@{UB} with an empty clock port
   * @{B}AmigaOS 2.04@{UB} or higher
   * about 5MB of hard disk space

@{I}2. SUPPORT@{UI}

@{B}Delfina  1200@{UB}  fully  supports  @{B}AHI@{UB},  the retargetable audio standard for @{B}Amiga@{UB}.
Number  of  @{B}AHI@{UB}  supporting  programs  is  steadily increasing. @{B}Delfina@{UB} also has
emulation for the @{B}Toccata@{UB} card.

In  addition  to  @{B}AHI@{UB}  standard,  @{B}Delfina  1200@{UB} can run multiple @{B}Delfina@{UB} and @{B}AHI@{UB}
programs  at  the same time, and various effects can be applied to any program's
output.  If multiple programs are producing sound, @{B}Delfina@{UB} will mix the outputs.
Only @{B}Delfina@{UB}'s DSP usage and internal memory set the limits.

Software supporting @{B}Delfina@{UB} includes:
   * @{B}Octamed SoundStudio@{UB}
   * @{B}AudioLab16@{UB} for @{B}Delfina@{UB}
   * @{B}SoundFX@{UB}
   * @{B}Digi Booster Pro@{UB}
   * @{B}Hippoplayer@{UB}
   * @{B}APlayer@{UB}
   * @{B}SinED@{UB}
   * @{B}Play 16@{UB}
   * @{B}ShapeShifter@{UB}
   * @{B}Fusion@{UB}
   * and many more.

@{B}Delfina 1200@{UB} system software includes:
   * @{B}AHI@{UB} (@{B}Audio Hardware Interface@{UB}) driver
       - Play&record multiple channel audio
       - @{B}AHI@{UB}  standard  allows  you  to  write software that works on other audio
         boards or normal @{B}Amiga@{UB} audio too
   * delfina.library
       - For basic operations and user's own @{B}DSP@{UB} software
       - Supports @{B}DSP@{UB} program multitasking
       - Enables audio playback and recording
   * DelfPrefs
       - Utility to adjust @{B}Delfina@{UB}'s parameters
   * DelFX
       - Multiple realtime effects
       - Record and play AIFFstereo samples at 4000-96000 Hz
       - Configurable shortcut effect combinations
       - Can be used to process input or output of other programs
   * DelfLoad
       - Shows DSP usage and other statistics
   * @{B}MUI 3.8@{UB} unregistered version
       - licensed for use with @{B}Delfina@{UB} software
   * A56
       - @{B}DSP56002@{UB} assembler
       - Allows you to write your own DSP programs
   * Many example programs including source code
   * Software upgrades available for free, at @{B}http://www.sci.fi/~petsoff/ftp/@{UB}

