@node not03 "DICE DEVELOPERS WANTED"

@{B}DICE@{UB} DEVELOPERS WANTED
----------------------

@{I}FOR INMEDIATE RELEASE@{UI}

@{B}DICE@{UB}  is a freely distributable @{B}C@{UB} compiler environment for the @{B}Amiga@{UB} computer by
@{I}Matt  Dillon@{UI}.  It  started off life as shareware but became a commercial product
published  by @{B}Obvious Implementations Corporation@{UB}. With the decline in the @{B}Amiga@{UB}
market, @{I}Matt@{UI} released the source code to @{B}DICE@{UB} in 1997.

This is where @{I}Richard Drummond@{UI} came in.

@{I}Richard@{UI}  perceived  an  interest still remaining in the @{B}Amiga@{UB} community for @{B}DICE@{UB}
and  in  October  of this year he produced a cleaned-up release of @{B}DICE@{UB} based on
@{I}Matt@{UI}'s  source.  As  a  result @{I}Richard@{UI} received enthusiastic responses from many
@{B}Amiga@{UB}  users.  So, with @{I}Matt Dillon@{UI}'s help, he set up the @{B}DICE Development Group@{UB}
to continue work on @{B}DICE@{UB}.

The  @{B}Dice Development Group@{UB} would like any programmers wanting to help with @{B}DICE@{UB}
overhaul to join.

@{B}Dice@{UB} will be a totaly free compiler with source.

New features:
  * Compiler optimisations
  * @{B}PPC@{UB}/@{B}C++@{UB}
  * Your suggestions.

Mail @{I}Richard Drummond@{UI}:
@{I}dice@drummond.u-net.com@{UI}
or
@{I}Matthew Fletcher@{UI}:
