@node not16 "PETRO TYSCHTSCHENKO TO VISIT AUSTRALIA"

@{I}PETRO TYSCHTSCHENKO@{UI} TO VISIT AUSTRALIA
--------------------------------------

@{I}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE:@{UI}

Free for Re-Publication

Australia - December 1998

Contact/Reply to: @{I}Basil Flinter@{UI} @{I}flinter@tpg.com.au@{UI}

It  is  with  pleasure  that we announce that @{I}Petro Tyschtschenko@{UI}, head of @{B}Amiga
International@{UB}, will be visiting Australia in January 1999.

As  this  will  be  the  first  visit  to  Australia by any @{B}AMIGA@{UB} official since
@{B}Commodore@{UB}'s  demise  in  1994,  @{I}Petro Tyschtschenko@{UI} is keen to meet with as many
members of the @{B}Amiga@{UB} community as he can during his trip.

There  will  be  an  opportunity to meet Mr @{I}Tyschtschenko@{UI} in Perth on Saturday 9
January 1999, and at two meetings proposed for the following weekend in Sydney.

For  those  with  a  commercial  interest  in  the  @{B}Amiga@{UB}'s  future in Australia
(Australasia), there will be a business meeting in Sydney on Friday 15 January.

And  depending on the support shown, a daytime function (lunch will be optional)
is proposed for the general public on Saturday, 16 January.

Persons  wishing to meet @{I}Petro Tyschtschenko@{UI} should send an email to the contact
address  given  above,  putting:  `@{I}Petro@{UI}  Visit  Perth' or `@{I}Petro@{UI} Visit Business
Sydney'  or  `@{I}Petro@{UI}  Visit  General  Sydney'  as the Subject, according to which
meeting they would like to attend.

Then,  in  the  body  of the email, they should give some background information
about themselves, as well as any comments that they may care to make relating to
the @{B}Amiga@{UB}'s future in Australasia.

Even  if you can't attend, please email us with your comments. (In this case put
`@{I}Petro@{UI} Visit Comment Only' as the Subject).

Australia once had a vibrant @{B}Amiga@{UB} community.

An  overwhelming response to this posting will indicate that the @{B}Amiga@{UB} still has
a  future  in Australasia, and will send a strong message to @{I}Petro Tyschtschenko@{UI}
and @{B}Amiga Inc.@{UB} that they should do something about it.
@{I}Basil Flinter@{UI}
Coordinating the @{B}Amiga@{UB} in Australasia
