@{B}FAIRBROTHERS, INC.@{UB} ANNOUNCES CLEARANCE SPECIAL
----------------------------------------------

@{I}Press Release@{UI}:

Audio Gallery for $9.95.

@{B}Audio  Gallery@{UB}  is available in English (ESL), German, Spanish, French, Italian,
Portuguese, Russian, Chinese, Japanese and Korean.
English/Romance  is  for  Spanish,  French,  German, Italian, Portuguese, Dutch,
Danish, Swedish, Norwegian, Finnish and Polish speakers.
English/Oriental is for Japanese, Korean and Chinese speakers.

I  am  trying  to clear out the basement of about 900 boxes of @{B}Audio Gallery 1.0@{UB}
(yes,  I  am  actually  working on a Version 2.0 of @{B}Audio Gallery@{UB} for the @{B}Amiga@{UB},
with  improved  graphics, some 3-D stuff, better sound quality, music, etc. (all
the things that the @{B}PC@{UB} copied from us)).

@{B}Audio  Gallery@{UB},  if  you  don't  remember, was the world's first talking picture
dictionary  (1989)  using  digitized  speech  and  graphics, thanks to the @{B}Amiga@{UB}
technology.  Thousands  of  these were sold at prices ranging up to $129.95 each
(unfortunately,  @{B}Fairbrothers@{UB}  invested  in  @{B}Commodore@{UB}  stock), but now they are
being offered for $9.95 each.

Available  on  CD-ROM (CD + diskette) or Diskette (7-8 diskettes), @{B}Audio Gallery@{UB}
is  a  talking  picture  dictionary,  a  good introduction to learning a foreign
language,  and  a  vocabulary  builder. @{B}Audio Gallery@{UB} uses the "Duden" method of
teaching  native  language that has been used for several decades in Germany and
Japan.  The  "Duden"  or picture dictionary, lays a good learning foundation for
schoolchildren,   and   is   a   reflection   of   how  these  countries  became
technologically advanced.

@{B}Audio Gallery@{UB} features digitized speech by native speakers. Spanish is done by a
native  Bolivian,  Chinese is the Mandarin dialect (Taiwanese accent), French is
Parisian-accented.

@{B}Audio  Gallery@{UB}  includes  about  thirty  colorful,  everyday  scenes. Each scene
includes  about  thirty  key words - numbered objects in the Scene. Click on the
object  to  hear  its pronunciation and see the written form in both English and
the foreign language.

Scenes  include:  Weather,  Supermarket,  Basic  Expressions,  Numbers, Clothes,
Living Room, Restaurant, Around the Town, and many others.

For  reference,  @{B}Audio Gallery@{UB} includes an on-line dictionary; quizzes test your
progress. A grammar manual is included, and for Chinese and Spanish, a workbook.

@{B}Audio  Gallery@{UB}  is  available  in  Korean,  Japanese, Chinese, Russian, Spanish,
German, French, English, Italian, and Portuguese.

The  updated English-Romance version speaks in English and shows translations in
Spanish, German, Italian, Portuguese, French, Danish, Dutch, Norwegian, Finnish,
Polish,  Russian, Swedish and Indonesian. The English-Oriental version speaks in
English  and  translates  into  Japanese  or Chinese. The English-Korean version
speaks in English and shows translations in English and Korean.

Check it out at @{B}http://www.fairbrothers.com/ag.htm@{UB}

Hope @{B}Gateway@{UB}/@{B}AI@{UB} comes through - 1999 will be the year of the "Wonder" @{B}Amiga@{UB}.

