@node not32 "THE WORLD FOUNDRY LEAVE VULCAN SOFTWARE"

@{B}THE WORLD FOUNDRY@{UB} LEAVE @{B}VULCAN SOFTWARE@{UB}
---------------------------------------

@{B}The World Foundry@{UB} - @{I}Official Press Release@{UI} - 16th December 1998

Today it has been confirmed that our company has parted from @{B}Vulcan Software@{UB} and
@{B}Vulcan@{UB}  will not be publishing @{B}Explorer 2260@{UB} for the @{B}Amiga PPC@{UB}. This is entirely
our own decision and has not been in anyway forced by @{B}Vulcan@{UB}.

Here is a short FAQ to cover most of the questions that we expect to be asked.

@{I}@{B}Q.@{UB} What were the reasons for @{B}TWF@{UB} to leave @{B}Vulcan@{UB} ? @{UI}
@{B}A.@{UB}  We  have  different opinions on the current market and community, as well as
different  plans  for  the  future. This is an amicable split and we wish @{B}Vulcan@{UB}
well with their future @{B}PC@{UB} software titles.

@{I}@{B}Q.@{UB} What effect will this have on @{B}Explorer2260@{UB} for the @{B}Amiga@{UB} ?@{UI}
@{B}A.@{UB} None whatsoever. Development of @{B}Explorer2260 PPC@{UB} and the @{B}Explorer Universe@{UB} is
continuing  as  normal  and  will  continue  till the title is finished. We have
updated the game specifications last week to state that we would be using @{B}Warp3D@{UB}
to provide 3D hardware accelerated performance.

@{I}@{B}Q.@{UB} I think @{B}Explorer@{UB} is vapour, why should I care ?@{UI}
@{B}A.@{UB}  Fair enough. If you want to believe that, it's your opinion. It's wrong, but
it's  yours.  I'm  sure  that  the 18 people working on it in various capacities
would agree with you whole heartedly.

@{I}@{B}Q.@{UB}  You're  going  to  cancel  the  title  eventually anyway and do a @{B}PC@{UB} version
instead, aren't you ?@{UI}
@{B}A.@{UB}  Absolutely  not.  If  we  had  any plans to do that we would not have parted
company with @{B}Vulcan@{UB}.

@{I}@{B}Q.@{UB} When will we see a demo/screenshots ?@{UI}
@{B}A.@{UB} The first images of the graphic engine should be seen in the first quarter of
1999. We apologies for no pictures of the game before this (bar the renders used
of  ship  designs  and  aliens in our game encyclopedia) but the code for the 3D
engine  is  in  no state to be shown unless people care for sexy pictures of the
code.

@{I}@{B}Q.@{UB} When is it due to be finished ?@{UI}
@{B}A.@{UB}  We  will try and aim for a 3rd quarter release although this could well fall
back into the 4th quarter.

@{I}@{B}Q.@{UB} How will @{B}Explorer@{UB} be published now ?@{UI}
@{B}A.@{UB} That will be determined closer to it's completion.

